PUH-BrianMartell Hopf Solitons — Understandable Explanation Hopf solitons are stable, particle-like knotted configurations of fields in 3+1 dimensions, characterized by the Hopf invariant Q_H — a topological linking number between pre-images of points on the target space. Simple picture: •  Field maps physical space to S² (or similar). •  Pre-images of two points form closed loops in space. •  Q_H = linking number of those loops — integer, conserved. •  Unlike skyrmions (π₃ topology), Hopf solitons use π₃(S²) = ℤ — allow true knots and links. In PUH v25, direct resonance: •  Substrate excitations can form 3D knotted twists with linking (higher topology than simple winding). •  Matter particles = minimal knots (Q_H = 1 or composites). •  Stability from lattice projection — linking prevents unwinding. •  Antimatter = opposite linking orientation. •  Annihilation = unlink → topology zero → radiation. No extra fields — Hopf topology natural in 3D photon lattice knots.
